<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Andrew Mellon's policies as Secretary of the Treasury in the 1920s included:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Increasing taxes on the wealthy</option>
            <option letter="b">Reducing taxes and government spending</option>
            <option letter="c">Expanding government welfare programs</option>
            <option letter="d">Nationalizing major industries</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Andrew Mellon, Treasury Secretary under Harding, Coolidge, and Hoover, advocated for reducing federal taxes and government spending. His policies, known as "scientific taxation," dramatically cut tax rates for the wealthy, believing this would stimulate economic growth. His conservative fiscal policies epitomized the pro-business orientation of Republican administrations during the 1920s.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
